! Architecture

!! Layers

# ''file-upload'' (existing) — `<$file-dropzone>` posts the binary to `/api/file-upload-binary`. Server-side MIME-checks against `$:/config/rimir/file-upload/media-types`, computes content hash, routes by MIME via `helpers.js:getSubfolderForType` (msg-import adds `application/vnd.ms-outlook → email/`), writes to `files/email/<filename>.msg`.
# ''file-pipeline'' (existing) — after upload, `widgets/dropzone.js:triggerPipeline()` posts to `/api/file-pipeline`. `pipeline-executor.js` matches `msg.tid` by MIME and runs its steps.
# ''msg-import'' (this plugin) — contributes `pipelines/msg.tid` and the two runner-actions `convert-msg-body` / `extract-msg-attachments` (merged into `runner-actions.json`).
# ''runner'' (existing) — executes the Python extractor `scripts/extract.py`. Pipeline-executor passes `{{input}}` and `{{output}}` as auto-quoted absolute paths.
# ''frontmatter'' (existing) — deserializes the `text/x-frontmattered-markdown` artifact tiddler's YAML header into tiddler fields; the save patch writes them back to `.md` on disk.

!! Data flow

```
drop .msg
  └─▶ file-upload → files/email/<file>.msg + parent tiddler
        └─▶ file-pipeline (MIME match)
              ├─ convert       → captureStdout → .email tiddler (markdown + YAML)
              ├─ attachments   → scanDir       → .attachments/<name> tiddlers
              └─ summary (opt) → LLM           → .summary tiddler
```

!! On-disk layout for one email

```
files/email/
  meeting.msg                            ← parent
  _derived/
    meeting.msg/
      cid_<id>.png                       ← inline images (referenced from body)
      att_invoice.pdf                    ← non-inline attachment (artifact tiddler)
      att_agenda.docx
```

!! Cascade

* ''Delete'' — `routes/delete.js` recursively removes `_derived/<basename>/` (incl. nested pipeline products). `_artifact_source` tiddlers (`.email`, `.attachments/*`, optional `.summary`, and any tiddlers produced by nested pipelines like a PDF attachment's `.text` extraction) cascade via `file-upload/startup.js:cascadeDeleteArtifacts`, which walks the chain transitively from file-upload ≥ 0.1.21.
* ''Rename'' — `routes/rename.js` (file-upload ≥ 0.1.20) renames the `_derived/<basename>/` directory; artifact tiddlers follow via `cascadeRenameArtifacts`, which from 0.1.21 also rewires multi-level descendants (e.g. an attached PDF's thumbnail artifact).
* ''Delete confirm modal'' — from file-upload ≥ 0.1.21, deleting any tiddler with `_canonical_uri` opens a confirmation modal listing the full transitive cascade + every backlinking tiddler. The user can disable via `$:/config/rimir/file-upload/confirm-deletes`.

!! Attachments are first-class

Non-inline attachments are written to `_derived/<basename>/att_<safe-name>`, picked up by file-pipeline's `scanDir`, and turned into artifact tiddlers with `_artifact_source = <parent.msg>`. From file-pipeline ≥ 0.1.10 each artifact's `type` is inferred from the filename extension (was: every output got `image/png`). After creation, the new `rimir-file-pipeline-artifact-created` hook fires and the `nested-trigger-startup` module re-runs the matching pipeline for each artifact — so a PDF attachment gets its own thumbnail + text extraction, and an attached `.msg` gets its own `.email` recursively. Cycle protection: every recursive call carries a `seen` map of URIs already pipelined in the chain.

From file-pipeline 0.1.11 the artifact also inherits the source's `pa.parent` field (orga-apps' note-anchor), so for any cross-cutting query "what tiddlers live in this note" the attachments show up. UI-wise though, the attachments are not exposed as siblings of the email (see next section).

!! Outlook-style inline attachments (`body/email.tid`, ≥ 0.1.6)

The email's attachments are rendered at the ''top'' of the `.email` view. Two ViewTemplateBody cascades cooperate:

* ''`cascade/msg`'' — matches `[type[application/vnd.ms-outlook]]` → dispatches to `body/msg` (the parent .msg thumb / expand toggle).
* ''`cascade/email`'' (new in 0.1.6) — matches `[type[text/x-frontmattered-markdown]has[msg-subject]]` → dispatches to `body/email`.

`body/email` is the single source of truth for email rendering:

# Attachment row first — `[_artifact_source<msgParent>_artifact_type[attachment]]` where `msgParent = {!!_artifact_source}` (the .email's own `_artifact_source` points back at the .msg). The same .msg is the `_artifact_source` of every PDF/image attachment, so the filter naturally finds them.
# Markdown body second — `<$transclude $mode="block"/>` renders the .email's `text` field through the frontmatter parser (which forwards to tiddlywiki/markdown).

`body/msg` in "full" mode delegates: `<$tiddler tiddler=<<emailTitle>>><$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/msg-import/body/email"/></$tiddler>`. So whether the user clicks the .msg thumb in the wiki story river or opens the .email tiddler in a new tab (orga-apps' `#`-permalink pattern), they get the same view.

Tile fallback chain: `_thumbnail_uri` → inline `image/*` preview → 📄 emoji + filename. Click on a tile opens the file in a new tab.

Surface separation:

|orga-apps note attachment grid (`views/details.tid`) | Direct uploads only — `pa.parent[<note>]!has[_artifact_source]`. The `.msg` shows here. Its inner PDFs do not |
|`body/email.tid` Attachments row (top of email body) | Email's own children — `_artifact_source<msg>_artifact_type[attachment]`. The PDFs show here |

This mirrors how a mail client renders attachments — the email is one box on the desk, its enclosed files live inside the box — rather than spilling them out as separate desk items.

!! ViewTemplateBody cascade

Parent `.msg` tiddlers have `_canonical_uri` pointing at the binary on disk; TW's default body view shows the "Trying to load external content" fallback because no built-in viewer handles `application/vnd.ms-outlook`. msg-import 0.1.3 ships:

* ''`$:/plugins/rimir/msg-import/cascade/msg`'' — tagged `$:/tags/ViewTemplateBodyFilter`, `list-before` the file-upload `cascade/thumbnail`. Matches on `type == application/vnd.ms-outlook` and dispatches to a custom body template.
* ''`$:/plugins/rimir/msg-import/body/msg`'' — two-mode view sharing the file-upload state tiddler `$:/state/file-upload/view-mode/<title>`:
** ''thumb'' (default): renders `_thumbnail_uri` as a small image; click switches to "full".
** ''full'': transcludes the sibling `<title>.email` tiddler's body (markdown with frontmatter fields). Includes a back-to-thumb button.

The cascade is generic — clicking the thumbnail in TW's story river expands to the email body inline. Same template fires when orga-apps' attachment tile click opens the `.email` tiddler in a new tab via the `#`-permalink workaround for appify (see `tw-appify-permalink-workaround` memory).

!! Boundaries (not auto-handled)

* Inline image URLs in the markdown body are wiki-absolute (e.g. `/files/email/_derived/meeting.msg/cid_abc.png`). If a parent `.msg` is renamed, the body's image references are NOT rewritten — they still point at the old `_derived/<basename>/` directory until you re-import or hand-edit. Live with it for v0.1; revisit if it bites.
